  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries and at international levels. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key examples include:\n\n1. United States:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n2. European Union:\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD)\n\n3. International Standards:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\nThese regulations typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Monitor transactions\n- Report suspicious activities\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nThe goal is to detect and prevent financial crimes like money laundering, terrorist financing, and other illegal financial activities.",
